ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ValueRange: 23andme_id; allen_cell_id; bil_dataset_id; bil_doi; bil_neuron_id; bil_sub_id; biosamples_id; cellosaurus_id; cirm_id; clo_id; dandi_id; dbgap_id; ebisc_id; ecacc_id; ega_id; geo_dataset_id; geo_platform_id; geo_profile_id; geo_sample_id; geo_series_id; hc_id; hipsci_id; hpscreg_id; mvp_id; nemo_id; nihhesc_id; nki_rs_id; nrgr_bio_id; sigma_aldrich_id; study_bio_id; study_ind_id; uk_biobank_id; wikidata_id; other
Notes: Please use the appropriate code for the type of nrgr_alt_id submitted. If the type is not in the list of codes below, please use 'other' and use the nrgr_other_alt_id_type column to describe the type of nrgr_alt_id provided in the current row. 23andme_id=23andMe; allen_cell_id=Allen Institute; bil_dataset_id=Brain Image Library dataset; bil_doi=Brain Image Library DOI; bil_neuron_id=Brain Image Library traced neuron; bil_sub_id=Brain Image Library submission; biosamples_id=Biosamples; cellosaurus_id=Cellosaurus; cirm_id=California Institute for Regenerative Medicine; clo_id=Cell Line Ontology; dandi_id=Distributed Archives for Neurophysiology Data Integration; dbgap_id=dbGaP; ebisc_id=European Bank for induced pluripotent Stem Cells; ecacc_id=European Collection of Authenticated Cell Cultures; ega_id=European Genome Archive; geo_dataset_id=NCBI GEO dataset; geo_platform_id=NCBI GEO platform; geo_profile_id=NCBI GEO profile; geo_sample_id=NCBI GEO sample; geo_series_id=NCBI GEO series; hc_id=Human Connectome; hipsci_id=Human Induced Pluripotent Stem Cell Initiative; hpscreg_id=Human Pluripotent Stem Cell Registry; mvp_id=Million Veteran Program; nemo_id=Neuroscience Multi-Omic Archive; nihhesc_id=NIH Human Embryonic Stem Cell Registry; nki_rs_id=Nathan Kline Institute - Rockland Sample; nrgr_bio_id=NRGR biorepository sample; sigma_aldrich_id=Sigma-Aldrich; study_bio_id=study submitted biospecimen; study_ind_id=study submitted id with phenotypic data; uk_biobank_id=UK Biobank; wikidata_id=Wikidata; other=other external resource

Name of other external resource or database that nrgr_alt_id refers to. NOTE: Only use this field if the external resource or database does not already have a code in the list provided under nrgr_alt_id_type. Moreover, in this case the nrgr_alt_id_type should be 'other'.
